            <title>[FLINK-1215] FileSystem.initOutPathLocalFS can lead to race condition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-1215</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This can fail when concurrent tasks notice about deleting/creating the output directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seen in a travis log:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Failed tests: &lt;br/&gt;
  LocalExecutorITCase.testLocalExecutorWithWordCount:61 java.io.IOException: Output directory &apos;file:/tmp/wctext7874076083387578604.out&apos; could not be created. Canceling task...&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.flink.api.common.io.FileOutputFormat.open(FileOutputFormat.java:232)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.flink.api.java.record.io.CsvOutputFormat.open(CsvOutputFormat.java:261)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.flink.runtime.operators.DataSinkTask.invoke(DataSinkTask.java:172)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.flink.runtime.execution.RuntimeEnvironment.run(RuntimeEnvironment.java:245)&lt;br/&gt;
	at java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:745)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
